definition: to cut short/extinct/to disappear/to vanish/absolutely/by no means

sentences.english: Many old books are now out of print.

sentences.english: Long out of print, the Collection has finally been supplanted.
sentences.chinese: 這張絕版已久的合集如今終於有了替代品。

sentences.english: Her first novel is out of print now but you may find a second-hand copy.

sentences.english: Sometimes an out-of-print book could be worth its weight in gold.

sentences.english: There are also lots of out of print magazines and newspapers available for free.

to sell off/to get rid of in a sale
genuine/intact in original packaging (not locally assembled and packaged)
